    {
      "id": "s1-1",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Color Basics",
      "body": "| **Category**                     | **Description**                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                |\n|:---------------------------------|:-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| **Color Models**                 | **RGB**: Red, Green, Blue – additive model used in screens. <br> **HEX**: Hexadecimal color codes, e.g., #FFFFFF. <br> **HSL**: Hue, Saturation, Lightness – intuitive for color adjustments. <br> **HSV**: Hue, Saturation, Value – similar to HSL but with different brightness handling.    |\n| **Color Terminology**            | **Saturation**: Intensity or purity of a color. <br> **Hue**: The color type (e.g., red, blue). <br> **Lightness**: Brightness or darkness of a color. <br> **Opacity**: Transparency level of a color, often defined as alpha in RGBA.                                                        |\n| **Color Representation Formats** | **HEX**: `#RRGGBB` or `#RRGGBBAA` (with alpha). <br> **RGB**: `rgb(255, 255, 255)` <br> **RGBA**: `rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5)` <br> **HSL**: `hsl(120, 100%, 50%)` <br> **HSLA**: `hsla(120, 100%, 50%, 0.5)`                                                                                    |"
    },
